# TODO: black-brown coalition

@bbwr_majority
title: BBWR majority alone
subtitle: BBWR: [+ bbwr_r +]%
view-if: bbwr_r >= 50
on-arrival: chancellor = "Empty"; chancellor_party = "BBWR"; bbwr_in_government = 1; in_bbwr_majority = 1; pro_republic += 5; foreign_minister_party = "BBWR"; interior_minister_party = "BBWR"; justice_minister_party = "BBWR"; labor_minister_party = "BBWR"; reichswehr_minister_party = "BBWR"; economic_minister_party = "BBWR"; finance_minister_party = "BBWR"; agriculture_minister_party = "BBWR"; reichswehr_loyalty -= 0.05; 
achievement: majority_party

Finally, the BBWR can govern alone! Our long campaign of electioneering has paid off. We do not need to worry about coalition government; anything is possible. 

What will be Piłsudski’s decision?

- @pilsudski_majority_chancellor: Józef Piłsudski will stay as Prime Minister.

@pilsudski_majority_chancellor
view-if: not historical_mode or not bbwr_prussia
on-arrival: chancellor = "Piłsudski"; speaker_election_time = 1
go-to: ministries

Józef Piłsudski has become Prime Minister of the BBWR majority

@bbwr_minority
title: BBWR minority government
subtitle: BBWR: [+ bbwr_r +]%
view-if: bbwr_r < 50 and president == "Ignacy Mościcki"
on-arrival: chancellor = "Empty"; chancellor_party = "BBWR"; bbwr_in_government = 1; in_bbwr_minority = 1; pro_republic += 3; foreign_minister_party = "BBWR"; interior_minister_party = "BBWR"; justice_minister_party = "BBWR"; labor_minister_party = "BBWR"; reichswehr_minister_party = "BBWR"; economic_minister_party = "BBWR"; finance_minister_party = "BBWR"; agriculture_minister_party = "BBWR"; reichswehr_loyalty -= 0.03; 
achievement: minority_party

The BBWR will govern as a minority. This will require careful negotiation and compromise with other parties to pass legislation.

What will be Piłsudski’s decision?

- @pilsudski_minority_chancellor: Józef Piłsudski will stay as Prime Minister.

@pilsudski_minority_chancellor
on-arrival: chancellor = "Piłsudski"; speaker_election_time = 1
go-to: ministries

Józef Piłsudski will stay as Prime Minister.

@ministries

We can pick from any number of ministries. Controlling a ministry allows us to directly effect policy in that area. [? if in_left_front : Any ministry that we do not take will be given to the KPP. ?] [? if in_left_front and reichswehr_minister_party == "KPP" : If the KPP controls the Reichswehr Ministry, the army will most likely revolt. ?]

- #mins_1928
- #drop_mins_1928

@labor
title: Labor Ministry
subtitle: Taking the Labor Ministry is expected of us.
unavailable-subtitle: We do not have enough leverage.
tags: mins_1928
choose-if: leverage >= 5
view-if: labor_minister_party != "BBWR"
on-arrival: leverage -= 5; labor_minister_party = "BBWR"; labor_minister = "Wissell"
go-to: ministries

Rudolf Wissell of the BBWR has been appointed labor minister.

@interior
title: Interior Ministry
subtitle: Taking the Interior Ministry is expected of us. The Interior Ministry controls domestic security.
unavailable-subtitle: We do not have enough leverage.
